<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <%- include('../partials/hearderlink.ejs') %>
        <title>Document</title>
</head>

<body>
    <%- include('../partials/header.ejs') %>

        <div class="page-contect">
            <div class="breadcrumb">
                <img src="/media/banner/university.png" alt="breadcrumb" class="breadcrumb-bg">
                <div class="breadcrumb-content">
                    <h2>Yerevan Haybusak University</h2>
                    <ol>
                        <li><a href="/">Home</a></li>
                        <li><a href="/universities">University</a></li>
                        <li>Yerevan Haybusak University</li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="container">
                <div class="university-container">
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-lg-12 col-xl-7">
                            <div class="university-secation-image">
                                <img src="/media/icon/Yerevan-Haybusak-University.webp" alt="">
                            </div>
                            <h1 class="sub-heading">
                                Yerevan Haybusak Medical University
                            </h1>
                            <div class="university-info">
                                <p class="m-0"><strong>City:</strong> Yerevan</p>
                                <p class="m-0"><strong>Country:</strong> Armenia</p>
                                <p class="m-0"><strong>Established</strong> 1991 by Academician Levon Harutyunyan</p>

                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-lg-12 col-xl-5">
                            <p class="university-secation-heading">Get Free Counselling </p>
                            <%- include('../partials/contactform.ejs') %>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="university-about mt-5">
                    <h2 class="university-secation-heading">Why Choose Haybusak for MBBS / General Medicine</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                            <li>Accreditation & Recognition: Medical programs are all licensed and accredited by the
                                state. Graduates are given state diplomas.
                            </li>
                        </span>
                        <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                            <li>Several Mediums of Instruction: Medicine (General Medicine / MD) etc. are also offered
                                in English, Russian and Armenian, which is a positive attribute among the international
                                students.
                            </li>
                        </span>
                        <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                            <li>Clinical & Practical Training: The clinical chairs of the medical institute are located
                                in the most optimal medical centers, research institutes, dental clinics, and its own
                                polyclinic. Students are provided with practical training through lectures, labs,
                                practicals, and internship.
                            </li>
                        </span>
                        <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                            <li>Simulation & Skills Development: The university has been coming up with its simulation
                                center where medical students train.</li>
                        </span>
                        <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                            <li>Student Friendly International: International students are numerous; good support
                                system. The foreign students are accommodated in exams, programmes etc.
                            </li>
                        </span>
                    </ul>
                    <div class="row mt-4">
                        <div class="col-lg-12 col-xl-6">
                            <h2 class="university-secation-heading">Duration & Structure
                            </h2>
                            <ul>
                                <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                                    <li>
                                        General medicine (MBDS/MD equivalent)
                                    </li>
                                </span>
                                <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                                    <li>Stomatology (Dentistry)
                                    </li>
                                </span>
                                <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                                    <li>Pharmacy
                                    </li>
                                </span>
                                <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                                    <li>
                                        Natural Resource Management (distant and face-to-face) and Ecology.
                                    </li>
                                </span>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-lg-12 col-xl-6">
                            <h2 class="university-secation-heading">Courses / Specialties Offered in Medical Institute
                            </h2>
                            <ul>
                                <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                                    <li>
                                        General Medicine (MBBS / MD) course is 6 years, which consists of
                                        classroom/theoretical knowledge, and laboratory work, as well as clinical
                                        rotation/internship.</li>
                                </span>
                                <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                                    <li>The first 5 years will be mainly academic and theoretical; the last year(s) will
                                        be the clinical training/internship. </li>
                                </span>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <table class="table table-bordered table-striped align-middle mt-4">
                        <thead class="table-dark">
                            <tr>
                                <th>Component</th>
                                <th>Estimated Cost (USD)</th>
                                <th>Approx. in Indian Rupees*</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr>
                                <td>1st Year Tuition Fee</td>
                                <td><b>US$ 4,300–5,500</b></td>
                                <td>₹3.4–4.5 lakhs</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Tuition Fees in Subsequent Years (2–6)</td>
                                <td><b>US$ 3,800–5,000</b> annually</td>
                                <td>₹3–4.5 lakhs per year</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Hostel / Accommodation</td>
                                <td>US$ 700–1,000 per year (depending on facility)</td>
                                <td>₹50,000–70,000+ depending on exchange rate and amenities</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Living & Miscellaneous Costs</td>
                                <td>Varies by lifestyle; additional costs for books, transportation, insurance etc.</td>
                                <td>Variable</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                    <div class="row mt-4">
                        <div class="col-lg-12 col-xl-6">
                            <h2 class="university-secation-heading">Eligibility Criteria (for International / Indian
                                Students)
                            </h2>
                            <ul>
                                <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                                    <li>
                                        Minimum age: The age is estimated at 17 years in December at the time of
                                        admission.
                                    </li>
                                </span>
                                <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                                    <li>Academic Qualification: Higher secondary education (10+2) with Physics,
                                        Chemistry, and Biology subjects. Percentages required are minimum; usually about
                                        50% in PCB of general candidates.
                                    </li>
                                </span>
                                <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                                    <li>Entrance exam: NEET qualification is a prerequisite in case with Indian
                                        students.
                                    </li>
                                </span>
                                <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                                    <li>
                                        Documents: Normally consists of academic transcripts, passport, age
                                        verification, maybe a health certificate, language proficiency etc. (Check with
                                        university)
                                    </li>
                                </span>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-lg-12 col-xl-6">
                            <h2 class="university-secation-heading">Recognition / Accreditation & Post Graduate
                                Opportunities
                            </h2>
                            <ul>
                                <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                                    <li>
                                        Admitted by the appropriate education institutions in Armenia. Programs
                                        state‑accredited. </li>
                                </span>
                                <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                                    <li>Appearing in international lists (e.g. of medical universities) and presumably
                                        identifiable by the agencies (such as WHO, FAIMER, etc.) (It is important to
                                        consult the most recent lists of both India and your country)</li>
                                </span>
                                <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                                    <li>Upon graduation, students have an option of residency, PhD or work in hospital
                                        setting.</li>
                                </span>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <h2 class="university-secation-heading text-center">Advantages & Considerations</h2>
                    <h2 class="university-secation-heading">Advantages:
                    </h2>
                    <ul>
                        <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                            <li>
                                Reduced living as well as tuition fees than most of the western or even certain private
                                universities in the west.
                            </li>
                        </span>
                        <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                            <li>The ability to use a flexible medium of instruction (English is available) and make it
                                available to foreign students.

                            </li>
                        </span>
                        <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                            <li>Exposure to good clinical practice, particularly in late adulthood.
                            </li>
                        </span>
                        <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                            <li>
                                Recognized state diploma.
                            </li>
                        </span>
                    </ul>
                    <h2 class="university-secation-heading">Consideration:
                    </h2>
                    <ul>
                        <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                            <li>
                                Make sure that you are known in your home country and that you are able to pass
                                licensing exams (e.g., in India, see NMC/FMGE etc).

                            </li>
                        </span>
                        <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                            <li>Cost of living, visa, travelling arrangement etc shall be considered.
                            </li>
                        </span>
                        <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                            <li>Cost could be influenced by currency fluctuations.
                            </li>
                        </span>
                        <span><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                            <li>
                                Application period/capacity: early.
                            </li>
                        </span>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
        <%- include('../partials/footer.ejs') %>
</body>

</html>